# Azure Repos sync (monorepo → separate ADO repos)

Source of truth for CI is **Azure Repos `dev`**, not only local files or GitHub. When you change anything under these paths — especially **`azure-pipelines.yml`**, Docker/k8s files, or app source — **finish by mirroring every affected repo** in the same session (WSL), unless the user said **skip Azure sync**.

## Preferred: one command for all changed products

From repo root, **after `git commit` and before `git push origin dev`** (integration branch is **`dev`**, not **`main`**):

```bash
cd /mnt/c/Users/mahdi/OneDrive/theleetclub/monitoring-app   # or your WSL path to repo root

bash scripts/sync-changed-azure-repos.sh
```

That script runs **`sync-to-azure-dev.sh`** once per product folder (**alert**, **monitoring-app-v2**, **people-analytics-sync**) that appears in commits since **`merge-base(origin/dev, HEAD)`** (default; set **`AZURE_SYNC_UPSTREAM`** only if the monorepo uses a different upstream). **Always use this** when more than one product path may have changed, so you never push only one ADO repo.

## Manual: single repo

```bash
bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh monitoring-app-v2 monitoring-app-v2
bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh alert apps/alert-theleetclub-com
bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh people-analytics-sync people-analytics-sync
```

Mappings:

| Azure DevOps repo slug | Monorepo folder |
|------------------------|-----------------|
| `monitoring-app-v2` | `monitoring-app-v2/` |
| `alert` | `apps/alert-theleetclub-com/` |
| `people-analytics-sync` | `people-analytics-sync/` |

Requires **`azure.txt`** at repo root with PAT on **line 2** (after `azuredevops:` line). Requires **network**. Auth: **`scripts/ado-curl-auth.sh`**.

## Do not

- Sync **only one** ADO repo when the same commit batch touched **multiple** product folders — run **`sync-changed-azure-repos.sh`** (or the three **`sync-to-azure-dev.sh`** lines for each changed path).
- Stop after editing YAML or app code without running the sync step(s).
- Tell the user to “push to Azure” when this agent can run the script(s) above.

## If sync fails

- Fix auth (`azure.txt`), PAT scopes (**Code: Read & write**), or script errors; report the exact stderr.
- UI-only steps (e.g. **Authorize** secure files / service connections) still belong to the user — say what to click.
